Ctenomys yatesi, also called Yates' tuco-tuco, is a species of tuco-tuco native to Bolivia.  Only found near Roboré, Department of Santa Cruz, at an elevation of around 550 metres (1,800 ft), the species measures about 220 millimetres (8 3⁄4 in) in length and has soft hazel and grey hair.  It was named after Terry Yates, a former curator at the University of New Mexico.